The 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference has kicked off at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Midrand. The conference is brought to delegates in partnership with Liquid Telecom, with the company’s CEO Reshaad Sha delivering the keynote address. Other speakers at the conference include Connection Telecom CEO David Meintjes, Microsoft’s Kevin George, and Google Cloud Partner Siatik’s Brett StClair. Delegates will also hear from Teraco MD Jan Hnizdo, VMWare’s Dave Funnell, Huawei’s Marcus Tay, and Schneider Electric’s Derek Friend. In addition to this, the conference will feature discussions about moving your business to the cloud, involving experts from SAP, Oracle, and Mimecast. Delegates will also be treated to excellent exhibitions from South Africa’s top cloud and telecoms providers, including Liquid Telecom, Huawei, Connection Telecom, Axiz, and Microsoft. The conference has attracted over 1,000 IT executives from across South Africa and neighbouring countries. A look at the 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference, and what delegates are treated to, is shown below.                                            